 an active process through which the world is disclosed for us.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aAufmerksamkeit. 4aKognition. 4aMediation. 4aPhilosophie. 4aZugang. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aAttention.  aaccess.  acognition.  amediation.  aphilosophy.1 aBoer, Bas de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Michelle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDepraz, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Angelo, Diego, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Angelo, Diego, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHayes, Lauren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIshihara, Yuko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeón, Felipe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoaiza, Juan M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLópez, Betzamel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSandoval, Luis R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSatne, Glenda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchmetkamp, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegundo-Ortin, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomonova, Elizaveta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSolomonova, Elizaveta, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWeele, Cor van der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWehrle, Maren, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relat